						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of a cavern called the <hi rend="italic">gavi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Circa 14th century.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year Īśvara, [Bhādra]padā śu. 1. It cannot be verified.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift to a deity. It refers to Muḷivāḍa, Alama Rahuta and the <hi rend="italic">Aṟuvatuvakalu.</hi></p>						

